<TITLE> Abdul Awal Mintoo had bypass surgery in Bangkok: family </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 27 (bdnews24.com)Abdul Awal Mintoo, a former FBCCI president, had seven-hour bypass surgery at a Bangkok hospital, his family said Wednesday. Updates with details Mintoo who went to Thailand for a regular check-up was diagnosed with three blockages. Upon arriving in Bangkok, he immediately visited his doctor who urgently advised angioplasty. Within 48 hours, three stents were put in place, but due to complications, the procedure had to be repeated. However, Mintoo's condition remained critical and it was eventually decided that a bypass operation was the only option. He is currently in recovery following the operation.
